Japan’s NEC, Partners Work on New Power Grid, Nikkei Reports

-- B y   M a k o t o   M i y a z a k i
-- 
2011-10-04T03:46:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-04/nec-partners-working-to-develop-a-new-power-grid-nikkei-says.html
NEC Corp., the  University of Tokyo 
and Japan’s governmental research institute are working to
develop a new type of power network that would ease the
introduction of renewable energy, the Nikkei newspaper said.  The company and university are cooperating with the
Institute of Advanced Industrial Science and Technology, or AIST,
the Nikkei reported without saying where it got the information.
They formed a consortium to develop a concept called digital
grid, invented by Rikiya Abe, Tokyo University professor.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Makoto Miyazaki in Tokyo at 
 mmiyazaki8@bloomberg.net . 